</div><div class="t m0 x24 h1c yb9 ff13 fs7 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws56">doned him; or, perhaps, was it more likely that Mark had indeed</div><div class="t m0 x24 h1c yba ff13 fs7 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws57">changed into someone whom Paul could now trust?</div><div class="t m0 x22 h1b ybb ff14 fs7 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws58">Look back in your own life to where you utter<span class="ws0">l<span class="ws59">y blew it yet wer<span class="_ _3"></span><span class="ws0">e</span></span></span></div><div class="t m0 x22 h1b ybc ff14 fs7 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">giv<span class="ws5a">en an opportunity to redeem yourself</span>.<span class="_ _c"> </span><span class="ws5b">How much did that</span></div><div class="t m0 x22 h1b ybd ff14 fs7 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws5c">new opportunity mean to you? How does that reflect,<span class="_"> </span><span class="ws0">in a small</span></div><div class="t m0 x22 h1b ybe ff14 fs7 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">wa<span class="_ _8"></span>y<span class="_ _3"></span>,<span class="_ _4"></span><span class="ws5d">the great principles of grace and forgi</span>veness that God gi<span class="_ _9"></span>v<span class="_ _3"></span>es</div><div class="t m0 x22 h1b ybf ff14 fs7 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws5e">to us? Maybe there’s someone whom you need to do the same</div><div class="t m0 x22 h1b yc0 ff14 fs7 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">for no<span class="_ _3"></span>w<span class="_ _8"></span>,<span class="_"> </span>as well? </div></div><div class="pi" data-data='{"ctm":[1.000000,0.000000,0.000000,1.000000,0.000000,0.000000]}'></div></div>
